    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>Thursday 14th Decr 64</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">To my great regret I found on<lb/> looking over the Biography a most
                awful<lb/> error rendering four pages useless. It has<lb/> originated from the
                extreme carelessness of the<lb/> person who made up the form. Please<lb/> see page
                25 herewith enclosed and compare<lb/> with Occident vol 22 no 5 p 205. I need<lb/>
                not point out to you how to correct the<lb/> error as you have the copy in the
                number<lb/> of the Occ. just mentioned. Should you<lb/> want to gain space you could
                print<lb/> from the words “The Hebrew level on p 205<lb/> of Occ. till “both ancient
                &amp; modern on p 207 of<lb/> Occ.—I am so hurried however that<lb/> I can only
                write you to reprint the<lb/> part in a cancel sheet<add>?</add>, for at
                present<lb/> the whole pamphlet is useless. I have<lb/> a<add>?</add> your letters,
                will reply to other forward<lb/> of yours to me when I send you Biography</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Please alter</p>
            <p>produced into</p>
            <p>procured on pge 25 of pamphlet</p>
        </body>
    </text>
